   ALUMINUM CO. OF AMERICA (Pittsburgh) -- George E.
Bergeron, 48 years old, was named vice president and general
manager of Alcoa's Rigid Packaging division, the company's
largest unit. Mr. Bergeron succeeds Thomas J. Taylor, 59, who
will assume a newly created position for sales, trading and
recycling in Alcoa's metals and chemicals group. Mr. Bergeron
had been president of Alcoa's closure systems unit since
1982.
